{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f72addc8-c46c-41c0-94ab-9fefde41289c","content":"Here's a quick overview of common web API templates and auth options:\n\n### .NET (dotnet)\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth [option]\n```\n**Auth options:** `None`, `Individual` (Identity/JWT), `IndividualB2C` (Azure AD B2C), `SingleOrg` (Azure AD), `MultiOrg`, `Windows`\n\n### Node.js / Express\nUse `express-generator` or frameworks like NestJS. Auth via **Passport.js** (JWT, OAuth2, API keys) or libraries like `jsonwebtoken`.\n\n### Python / FastAPI\n```bash\npip install fastapi[all]\n```\nAuth via **OAuth2 with JWT**, API keys, or session-based auth.\n\n### Java / Spring Boot\nUse [start.spring.io](https://start.spring.io) with **Spring Security**. Supports JWT, OAuth2, Basic Auth, LDAP.\n\n---\n\nWant me to scaffold a project for a specific framework? If so, let me know which stack and auth type you'd like.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"89717839-add9-4ee8-91aa-2dee70f031b3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most common frameworks.","outputTokens":311,"requestId":"280E:2CC3E:12827B:18567C:69FFD7A8"},"id":"fec2180d-7740-469e-afad-d3a823997839","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:56:18.894Z","parentId":"92cf0656-5ca5-4dfa-8cfa-ad54e9f64e62"}
